<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>CAMERON JAGGER — A Project Built by Hand — VERRE</title>
  <style>
    :root{
      --bg:#ffffff;
      --text:#111111;
      --muted:#666666;
      --line:#dddddd;
      --max:820px;
      --quote:#0f0f0f;
      --soft:#fafafa;
    }

    *{ box-sizing:border-box; }

    body{
      margin:0;
      background:var(--bg);
      color:var(--text);
      font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      line-height:1.65;
    }

    .page{
      width:100%;
      padding:40px 20px 80px;
    }

    .article{
      max-width:var(--max);
      margin:0 auto;
    }

    .eyebrow{
      font-size:12px;
      letter-spacing:0.12em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      color:var(--muted);
      margin-bottom:14px;
    }

    h1{
      font-size:clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
      line-height:1.05;
      margin:0 0 12px;
      font-weight:700;
      text-transform:uppercase;
    }

    .dek{
      font-size:1.05rem;
      color:var(--muted);
      max-width:720px;
      margin:0 0 24px;
    }

    .meta{
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:10px;
      margin:0 0 26px;
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:0.9rem;
    }

    .chip{
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:8px 10px;
      background:#fff;
    }

    .hero-image,
    .inline-image{
      width:100%;
      margin:28px 0;
    }

    .hero-image{ margin:0 0 28px; }

    .hero-image img,
    .inline-image img{
      width:100%;
      display:block;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:#f3f3f3;
      object-fit:cover;
    }

    .hero-image img{ aspect-ratio:16 / 10; }
    .inline-image img{ aspect-ratio:16 / 10; }

    figcaption{
      font-size:0.8rem;
      color:var(--muted);
      margin-top:8px;
      line-height:1.4;
    }

    .intro{
      font-size:1.04rem;
      margin-bottom:34px;
    }

    .section{
      border-top:1px solid var(--line);
      padding-top:26px;
      margin-top:26px;
    }

    .section h2{
      margin:0 0 10px;
      font-size:0.85rem;
      letter-spacing:0.14em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      color:var(--muted);
      font-weight:700;
    }

    .pull{
      margin:14px 0 14px;
      padding:18px 18px;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:var(--soft);
    }

    .pull .quote{
      margin:0;
      font-size:1.2rem;
      line-height:1.35;
      font-weight:700;
      color:var(--quote);
    }

    .pull .attrib{
      margin:10px 0 0;
      font-size:0.78rem;
      letter-spacing:0.08em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      color:var(--muted);
    }

    .body{
      margin:0 0 12px;
    }

    .closing{
      border-top:1px solid var(--line);
      margin-top:42px;
      padding-top:28px;
      font-size:1.02rem;
    }

    .footer-note{
      margin-top:22px;
      font-size:0.85rem;
      color:var(--muted);
    }

    a{
      color:inherit;
      text-decoration:underline;
      text-decoration-color:#cfcfcf;
    }
    a:hover{ opacity:0.8; }

    @media (max-width:640px){
      .page{ padding:24px 16px 56px; }
      .intro, .closing{ font-size:0.98rem; }
      .pull .quote{ font-size:1.08rem; }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <main class="page">
    <article class="article">

      <div class="eyebrow">VERRE Feature</div>
      <h1>Cameron Jagger</h1>

      <p class="dek">
        A project built by hand by Travis Jagger and Cameron Mangus — started in Summer 2025 at ages
        15 and 17. Every piece is made in-house, with a focus on control, intention, and refusing
        the shortcuts of a corporatized fashion pipeline.
      </p>

      <div class="meta">
        <span class="chip">Palm Desert → Los Angeles</span>
        <span class="chip">Est. 2025</span>
        <span class="chip">Made in-house</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Replace image paths with your real files -->
      <figure class="hero-image">
        <img
          src="assets/archive/cameron-jagger-2026-03-__/cj-1.jpg"
          alt="Cameron Jagger at the collection release event"
        />
        <figcaption>CAMERON JAGGER at their collection release / multi-media exhibition in Los Angeles.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <section class="intro">
        <p class="body">
          CAMERON JAGGER is a creative project that treats each collection as a technical and artistic
          improvement—without outsourcing the soul of the work. From patterning to sewing, the process
          is carried out by the founders themselves, using high-quality fabrics with an emphasis on
          ethically produced and sourced materials.
        </p>
        <p class="body">
          What stood out most wasn’t just the garments—it was the clarity of their mindset: a willingness
          to learn fast, take risks early, and protect the integrity of how the clothes are made.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- SECTION 1 -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Origin</h2>

        <div class="pull">
          <p class="quote">“We both felt a very unsettling lack of fulfilment… it felt like a literal existential threat.”</p>
          <p class="attrib">Cameron Jagger</p>
        </div>

        <p class="body">
          Starting young didn’t feel optional to them—it felt urgent. That urgency became the catalyst
          for committing early and building something real, day by day.
        </p>
      </section>

      <figure class="inline-image">
        <img
          src="assets/archive/cameron-jagger-2026-03-__/cj-2.jpg"
          alt="Garments on rack at Cameron Jagger event"
        />
        <figcaption>Garments presented at the event (replace with your rack photo).</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <!-- SECTION 2 -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Process</h2>

        <div class="pull">
          <p class="quote">“Ultimately, it’s the idea… the steps of the process, from patterning to sewing, all serve the idea.”</p>
          <p class="attrib">Cameron Jagger</p>
        </div>

        <p class="body">
          Their process isn’t about picking a single “most important” step—it’s about preserving the
          original concept through every stage, refining it until the finished piece matches the idea
          as closely as possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- SECTION 3 -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Non-negotiables</h2>

        <div class="pull">
          <p class="quote">“As we grow, we will refuse to let go of our own manufacturing… The clothes will forever be made on our terms.”</p>
          <p class="attrib">Cameron Jagger</p>
        </div>

        <p class="body">
          The line is clear: no outsourcing the core. Their manufacturing stays in their control—because
          control is the point. Not scale for scale’s sake.
        </p>
      </section>

      <figure class="inline-image">
        <img
          src="assets/archive/cameron-jagger-2026-03-__/cj-3.jpg"
          alt="Attendees holding Cameron Jagger pieces"
        />
        <figcaption>Supporters showing love with pieces in-hand (replace with your best “people holding clothes” shot).</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <!-- SECTION 4 -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Moving early</h2>

        <div class="pull">
          <p class="quote">“We will do just about anything to get into rooms we should by zero means be in.”</p>
          <p class="attrib">Cameron Jagger</p>
        </div>

        <p class="body">
          They describe operating off willpower—trying “random shit until something works.” The biggest
          lesson: age doesn’t limit capability, even if people try to make it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <figure class="inline-image">
        <img
          src="assets/archive/cameron-jagger-2026-03-__/cj-4.jpg"
          alt="Crushh with Cameron Jagger founders"
        />
        <figcaption>Crushh with the founders (replace with your photo). Use this as your “scene overlap” proof.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <!-- SECTION 5 -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>What they want you to feel</h2>

        <div class="pull">
          <p class="quote">“I hope people understand the thought, love, time, and intentionality… This isn’t some shitty, meaningless money grab.”</p>
          <p class="attrib">Cameron Jagger</p>
        </div>

        <p class="body">
          The clothing is described as intimate—something that carries personal weight when worn. The
          stakes are real too: building without a trust fund, taking on debt, and choosing the harder
          path because it “needs to happen.”
        </p>

        <div class="pull">
          <p class="quote">“We go into ridiculous amounts of debt to make this shit happen because it needs to happen.”</p>
          <p class="attrib">Cameron Jagger</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="closing">
        <p class="body">
          CAMERON JAGGER’s story isn’t just “young designers making clothes.” It’s a commitment to
          authorship—controlling the process, protecting the idea, and building a world around the work.
        </p>

        <p class="footer-note">
          VERRE — more features at <a href="https://verre.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">verre.us</a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </article>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
